# Todo CLI Application

A simple command-line interface (CLI) todo application with in-memory storage, built with Python.

## Features

- Interactive menu-driven interface with numbered options (1-6 + 0 to exit)
- Add new tasks with titles and optional descriptions
- View all tasks with their ID, title, description, and completion status
- Mark tasks as complete or incomplete
- Update existing tasks' titles and descriptions
- Delete tasks by ID

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.13 or higher
- UV package manager (optional but recommended)

## Installation

1. Clone the repository
2. Install dependencies (if any) with pip

## Usage

### Interactive Mode (Recommended)
```bash
python src/cli/main.py
```

### Command Line Mode
```bash
python -m src.cli.main --help
```

## Running with UV

### Setup
```bash
# Create virtual environment with UV
uv venv

# Activate the virtual environment
source .venv/bin/activate

# Install the project in development mode
uv pip install -e .
```

### Run the Application
```bash
# Run with UV
uv run python src/cli/main.py

# Or run the installed script
uv run todo
```

### Alternative UV Method
```bash
# Run directly with UV without installation
uv run --with setuptools src/cli/main.py
```

## Architecture

The application follows a clean architecture with clear separation of concerns:

- `models/task.py`: Contains the Task data model
- `services/task_manager.py`: Contains business logic and in-memory storage
- `cli/main.py`: Contains the interactive command-line interface

## Testing

To run the unit tests:
```bash
python -m unittest discover tests/unit/
```

To run the integration tests:
```bash
python -m unittest discover tests/integration/
```

## Limitations

- Data is stored only in memory and will be lost when the application exits
- No persistent storage
- Single-user application
